{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Why\nCollapse the agent's monitoring to ONE call returning ONE typed outcome, so agents never correlate votes/labels/status — and the \"both votes green but conflicts\" trap is handled inside the tool, not by every session.\n\n## What\nA project command (project CLI/script, NOT `rebar` core; may `import rebar` only for ticket ops) that requests a land and returns one typed terminal outcome + distinct exit code. Blocking `--wait` + single-shot `land-status`.\n\n## Dependencies\nDepends on **S1** (`sterilized-papery-horse`, 843b-801f-9ef9-442d) — the `Autosubmit` label, which `land` sets — and **S3** (`darksome-starry-sable`, 0525-6d71-8969-4512) — the recorded outcome, the authoritative source this command reads before falling back to native votes.\n\n**Interface dependency on S5** (`perpetual-ultrasonic-raccoon`, 3c55-2af3-0c9c-4b11): the `lander_down` outcome reads the bot **heartbeat** that S5's deployed service emits (S5 AC5). This is a *heartbeat-contract* dependency — the heartbeat location (a timestamp file in the state volume or a health metric) plus the **90 s staleness threshold** defined below — NOT a build-order blocker: `land` is coded against that contract and does not need S5's deploy to be complete to be implemented and unit-tested.\n\n## Scope\nThe agent-facing command + the outcome enum contract. Lives in project tooling, not `src/rebar`.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `land <change> --wait` sets `Autosubmit` **under the agent's OWN Gerrit identity** (a Contributor — requires S1's requester-votable ACL; no bot-side voting endpoint), blocks until terminal, returns one typed outcome as JSON + a **distinct exit code per outcome** per this table: `0 merged`, `1 needs_rebase`, `2 ci_failed`, `3 review_failed`, `5 abandoned`, `6 lander_down`, `124 timed_out`, any other failure → `error` (nonzero, distinct from the above).\n- [ ] **`lander_down` (bot-SPOF liveness):** the single-instance bot is a SPOF; if it is down/wedged, `land --wait`/`land-status` must NOT hang to `timed_out`. Both read the bot **heartbeat** (the signal S5 emits per its AC5 heartbeat contract, written once per the bot's 15 s poll — see S2); if it is stale — **older than 90 s** (6× the 15 s poll, so a few consecutive slow iterations / a transient Gerrit hiccup do NOT trip a false `lander_down`) — they return the distinct `lander_down` outcome + exit code (`6`) IMMEDIATELY (within one `land` poll cycle, not after the 30-min timeout), with the message \"lander unavailable — rebase to tip and submit manually (see CONTRIBUTING §2e 'Submit', ADR-0040).\" The manual FFO rebase-and-submit is the sanctioned degraded path.\n- [ ] `land-status <change>` single-shot variant returns the same enum **plus a non-terminal `pending`** value while the bot is still driving (it does NOT set `Autosubmit` — that is `land`'s job; this resolves the fire-and-forget-then-check-back flow: run `land <change>` once, poll `land-status` which returns `pending` until terminal).\n- [ ] **`--wait` termination/timeout:** every 30s the poll loop consults BOTH (a) native Gerrit state via `GET /changes/{id}` for `merged`/`ci_failed`/`review_failed`/`abandoned` (MERGED / ABANDONED / a failing label), AND (b) the auto-lander's recorded outcome (S3, read via its status query — a read of its state dir / a small status endpoint) for `needs_rebase`, which is NOT derivable from native state (a behind-tip change is REST-submittable — `submittable=True` — yet not FFO-landable); it does NOT rely on `GET /changes/{id}` alone. A Gerrit **`ABANDONED`** status maps to the terminal `abandoned` outcome with its own distinct exit code (`5`); overall timeout 30 min → `timed_out` (exit `124`); transport errors are retried (bounded) before surfacing `error`.\n- [ ] **Fallback precedence** for deriving the outcome: (1) the bot's recorded outcome (S3) wins if present; else derive from native Gerrit state — `Verified -1` → `ci_failed`, `LLM-Review -1` → `review_failed`, MERGED → `merged`, `ABANDONED` → `abandoned`; if both `-1` are present with no bot record, `ci_failed` wins. **`needs_rebase` is NOT derivable from native state** — a behind-tip change is **REST-submittable** (`submittable=True`) but not **FFO-landable**, and returns a fast-forward-only \"not fast-forward\" error only on the submit *attempt*, so `needs_rebase` requires the bot's recorded outcome (S3); it never appears via native-state fallback.\n- [ ] Command lives in PROJECT tooling (repo CLI/script), NOT `rebar` core; may `import rebar` only for ticket ops (e.g. close the ticket on merge). No Gerrit-specific landing logic in `src/rebar`.\n- [ ] The outcome enum is documented as a **stable, versioned contract** at `docs/land-contract.md` — listing the enum values, the exit-code table, and a `contract-version`; `land --help` cites it. Agents depend only on this contract. (The ADR that records the overall auto-lander design and anchors this contract is authored downstream by S6, not here.)"}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783784533430710001,"uuid":"9aad7c9e-976d-416d-b87c-b18a35593b2b"}